3.2.3. Core level shifts
The Tm 4d core level has a multiplet structure due to 4f4d interactions [19] ,[20] . The variation of the Tm 4d core levels as a function of annealing temperature of the 2.3 ML thick Tm/Pt(1 1 1) layer, is shown in Fig. 5 . The main Tm 4d multiplet peak shifts by about 1.1 eV towards lower binding energy when heating the sample to 600 C. Subsequently, by heating the sample to 900 C, the peak shifts back by about 1.0 eV to higher binding energy relative to the peak position at 600 C. The shifts for the Tm 4d core level are approximately 0.2 eV larger than the shifts observed for the main 4f multiplet.
